Kiki Bertens on winning the St Petersburg ladies trophy following win over Donna Vekic
description:
Kiki Bertens gave her verdict on Sunday after clinching her third title in six months in a 7-6(2), 6-4 win over Donna Vekic in the final of the St. Petersburg Trophy.

Second-seeded Bertens came back from 5-2 down in the first set to win four straight games and force a tiebreak. Eighth-seeded Vekic saved three match points in the second set before Bertens closed out the match for her eighth career title.

The win continued Bertens' emergence as a more versatile player. Until she beat Simona Halep to win the Cincinnati Open in August, Bertens had never reached a WTA final on any surface other than clay, but she has now won three straight hard-court finals.

Bertens' current ranking of eighth is the highest for a Dutch woman since Betty Stove, who reached No. 5 in 1977.

title: Barcelona train and talk ahead of Copa del Rey semi-final with Real Madrid
description:
Lionel Messi has returned to training, a day before Barcelona host Real Madrid in the first leg of the semifinals of the Copa del Rey.
Messi was sidelined from Monday's training session because of a right leg injury sustained in a Spanish league match on Saturday.
He re-joined his teammates on the practice field on Tuesday and showed no signs he was bothered by the injury.
The media could only watch the first few minutes of the session, when players warmed up and played keep-away.
Coach Ernesto Valverde had said earlier on Tuesday he would wait for the training session to end before deciding whether Messi will play on Wednesday at Camp Nou Stadium.

title: Australia beat Bosnia Herzegovina 4-0 to book their place in the Madrid finals
description:
Australia completed a 4-0 win over Bosnia Herzegovina on Saturday, to clinch their place in the inaugural 18-nation Davis Cup final in Madrid, Spain later this year.

Opening day singles successes for John Millman and Alex de Minaur ensured that Australia held a commanding 2-0 lead ahead of day two - and crucially ensured that Bosnia had no further room for error.

The hosts built on that lead in the hot Adelaide sun.

John Peers and Jordan Thompson combined well to beat Tomislav Brkic and Mirza Basic 7-5 6-1 in the doubles rubber, giving Australia an unassailable 3-0 lead.

Then Davis Cup debutant Alexei Popyrin beat Nerman Fatic, cruising through the opening set before fending off a decent challenge in the second set to take a 6-1 7-6(2) victory.

title: Kagawa - I'm here for the food, beaches, and to score goals for Besiktas
description:
Japanese midfielder Shinji Kagawa was presented to the media by Besiktas in Istanbul on Tuesday after his loan move from Borussia Dortmund to the Turkish side.
Kagawa has already made an impact at the club, coming on as a substitute in the 81st minute against Antalyaspor on Sunday and scoring twice in two minutes on his debut, as his new team completed a 6-2 win.
The 29-year-old has joined on loan until the end of the season.

title: Real Madrid prepare for first leg of Copa del Rey semi-final with Barcelona
description:
Real Madrid manager Santiago Solari spoke to the media on Tuesday, as his side continued their preparations for the first leg of their Copa del Rey semi-final tie, away at La Liga leaders Barcelona on Wednesday.
The fixture will be Solari's first 'Clasico' in charge of Real Madrid, but is the first of three matches between the rivals in less than a month.
The last time the two sides met Barcelona thrashed Madrid 5-1, a result that prompted the sacking of former coach Julen Lopetegui after just three months in charge.
Barcelona have remained silent about Lionel Messi's health and whether he will feature in the semi-final, following an injury to his right leg sustained on Saturday during a 2-2 draw with Valencia.

title: Rookie forward Marvin Bagley leads Kings over Spurs, 127-112
description:
Rookie forward Marvin Bagley III had a career-high 24 points and 12 rebounds for his third straight double-double, leading the Sacramento Kings past the San Antonio Spurs 127-112 on Monday, for their seventh straight home win.

De'Aaron Fox added 20 points and Buddy Hield scored 18 to extend Sacramento's longest home winning streak since a 14-gamer in 2005-06.

That was the last time the Kings made the playoffs, but Sacramento could make a run at a postseason spot this season.

The Kings trail the Los Angeles Clippers by a half-game for eighth place in the Western Conference.

DeMar DeRozan had 24 points and LaMarcus Aldridge added 22 for the Spurs.

Sacramento had lost 14 straight to San Antonio before the win in November.

The teams meet for their final regular season game in March in Texas.

title: Data preview to Atletico vs Real Madrid in La Liga
description:
Atletico Madrid host Real Madrid in a genuine six-pointer at the top of La Liga. Victory for Atletico would put them five points clear of their cross-city rivals in second place, as Diego Simeone's men try to keep pace with leaders Barcelona.
The last three league encounters between these two have ended in draws.

title: Eng Sub: Osaka fans celebrate in Tokyo
description:
Japanese fans celebrated Naomi Osaka's Australian Open title on Saturday, saying her historic win will serve as an inspiration to future generations.

Osaka beat Petra Kvitova 7-6 (2), 5-7, 6-4 to claim a second consecutive Grand Slam title.

On top of that, the 21-year-old will rise to No. 1 in the rankings.

Osaka, whose mother is Japanese and father is from Haiti, has been a star in Japan since she beat Serena Williams in the final of the last U.S. Open.

Osaka became the first woman to win back-to-back majors since Williams in 2015.

Osaka's performance at the Australian Open has topped daily news coverage in Japan.

title: Giannis Antetokounmpo scores 30 points as Bucks dominate Nets 113-94
description:
The Milwaukee Bucks defeated the Brooklyn Nets 113-94 at the Barclays Center in New York on Monday.

The Milwaukee Bucks outscored the Brooklyn Nets 23-17 in the first quarter.

Giannis Antetokounmpo led all players with 20 points in the first half as the Bucks led the Nets, 51-42.

The Nets shot a putrid 1-18 from the perimeter in the first half.

The Nets were unable to mount a second half comeback as the Bucks held on to a comfortable victory.

Giannis Antetokounmpo finished the game with 30 points, the most of any player.

title: Malaysia defiant despite losing Paralympic event after Israeli athlete ban
description:
Malaysia's government remains defiant after losing the rights to host the World Para Swimming Championships, having banned Israel from competing in the event.
The country's governments said earlier in January that no Israeli delegates can enter Malaysia for sporting or other events, in solidarity with Palestine.
The ban prompted the International Paralympic Committee (IPC) to withdraw Malaysia's hosting rights on Sunday.
Malaysian Prime Minister, Mahathir Mohamad, was unapologetic about the move when he spoke to media in Putrajaya on Monday.
The 2019 World Para Swimming Championships, which had been scheduled to take from 29th July to 4th August, is set to involve around 70 nations and will act as a qualifying competition for the 2020 Tokyo Paralympics.

title: Reaction from LeBron James after the worst loss of his career
description:
Bojan Bogdanovic scored 24 points as the Indiana Pacers tied an NBA franchise record by making 19 3-pointers in a 136-94 win over the Los Angeles Lakers on Tuesday, handing LeBron James the most lopsided loss of his career

James' teams have lost by 36 points twice previously.

James had 18 points, nine rebounds and seven assists in his second game back since injuring his groin on Christmas Day, but he didn't feature in the fourth quarter

The Lakers players were serenaded by Pacers fan about trade rumors all night long.

title: FIFA President Infantino pushes for Club World Cup and Global Nations League
description:
FIFA President Gianni Infantino on Thursday called for cooperation amongst football governing bodies at the opening of the UEFA Congress in Rome, where Aleksander Ceferin will be confirmed as the head of European football.
Infantino himself will be the only candidate in the FIFA presidential election scheduled for 5th June in Paris.
After the ballot formality in Rome, challenges will stack up for Ceferin — elite clubs demanding more Champions League money and FIFA wanting new competitions which could threaten UEFA's prized assets.
Infantino has been pushing his FIFA Council for almost a year to accept a secretive 25 billion US dollars offer from private investors.
They want to jointly run an expanded Club World Cup and worldwide Nations League — originally a UEFA idea — for 12 years from 2021.

title: D'Angelo Russell scores 27 points to help Nets beat Nuggets 135-130
description:
D'Angelo Russell had 27 points and 11 assists as the Brooklyn Nets surpassed last season's win total by beating the Denver Nuggets 135-130 on Wednesday night.

Russell made six of the Nets' 19 3-pointers, one game after they made only five as a team in their poorest shooting performance of the season.

Joe Harris chipped in 17 points for the Nets.

Brooklyn had failed to score 100 in its previous two games.

Nikola Jokic had 25 points, 14 rebounds and 10 assists in his 10th triple-double of the season for the Nuggets, who have lost two straight games to fall out of a tie for the Western Conference lead.

Mason Plumlee scored a season-high 24 points on 10-for-12 shooting against his former team.

title: Sao Paulo prepare for Copa Libertadores encounter with Talleres
description:
Three-times Copa Libertadores champions Sao Paolo trained on Tuesday on the eve of the first leg of their second round clash with Argentina's Talleres de Cordoba.
The best eight teams on phase two will qualify for an additional third round that will allow four teams to reach the Group stages of the 2019 Copa Libertadores.
Sao Paulo claimed three Copa Libertadores - in 1992, 1993 and 2005.
Their last trophy was the Copa Sudamericana, which they won in 2012 after defeating Argentina's Tigre 2-0 on aggregate in the final.
Talleres' only international victory, on the other hand, was in 1999 when they claimed the now defunct CONMEBOL Cup.
Wednesday's first leg match between Talleres and Sao Paulo will be played in Cordoba's Estadio Mario Alberto Kempes.

title: Harlem Globetrotters set numerous Guinness World Records
description:
The Harlem Globetrotters added five more Guinness World Records in one day to make it a total of 21, which includes one by a female player - a first for the group.

"I am so happy to be the first female (Harlem Globetrotter) to be in the Guinness World Records," said Cherelle 'Torch' George, after setting the record for most basketball under the leg tumbles in one minute by a female, with 32.

Bull Bullard, one of the team's star players, set a record with a 58 foot (17.7-metres) somersault basketball shot.

Zeus McClurkin also set the record for most blindfolded basketball slam dunks in one minute with a total of five.

The Harlem Globetrotters are currently on a world tour.

title: Brazil and Belgium tied at 1-1 in the 2019 Davis Cup qualifiers
description:
Brazil and Belgium are locked at one rubber each after the first day of the Davis Cup qualifying in Uberlandia in Brazil.

Thiago Monteiro had few problems against Arthur De Greef in the first of two singles matches– easing to a 6-3, 6-2 victory in an hour.

De Greef broke his racket in frustration as he was outclassed.

Yet Belgium won a vital rubber in the second match on court.

The European's beat Brazil at this stage in 2016 to reach the finals, and gave themselves hope of a repeat as Kimmer Coppejans beat Rogerio Dutra Silva in straight sets.

Closer than the first match, but Coppejans took the victory 6-4, 6-4.

title: Macarena Sanchez makes history with legal action for women
description:
Macarena Sanchez is taking legal action against her former club UAI Urquiza and the Argentina Football Association after she was released from her club for no reason.
The 27-year-old is demanding that the AFA make women's football professional in Argentina.    
"I want to be recognised as a professional player. I want to be taken as a professional athlete and this opens the doors for other girls so that they can also enjoy the benefits of working as football players, something that we love. We have to live with the current conditions. We have to show all the time that we can play, show that we know football. We have to make a lot more effort than the men and they (clubs and AFA) give us half of the things male players receive."
There is a long history of women's football in the country. This Argentina vs the hosts Mexico at the 1971 Women's World Cup
74-year-old Elba Selva was the 'Maradona' of the women's game and she has seen little change in attitudes.
They didn't looked at us in a good way. For example people would see a woman playing football and shout things to her, such as: 'Go wash the dishes!' But not all of them. There were some people who saw us doing kick ups or heading the ball or something like that and they applauded us and recognised that we could actually also play like men."
"It's not easy to be the first woman to initiate legal actions against the Argentina Football Association" says Sanchez. "It's a pretty big backpack that I have to put on. I knew it was going to have a lot of repercussion. I knew that I was going to find a lot of people who didn't support me. But well, in the balance, the people have spoken."

title: Records fall as Getaneh Molla and Ruth Chepngetich claim Dubai Marathon titles
description:
Ethiopian Getaneh Molla and Ruth Chepngetich of Kenya claimed the men's and women's titles, respectively, on a remarkable day at the Dubai Marathon on Friday.
Molla won in 2 hours, 3 minutes and 34 seconds, breaking the course record by 26 seconds while clocking the sixth-fastest men's marathon time ever.
Second-placed Herpassa Negasa ran 2:03:40, for the eighth fastest-ever marathon time, with Asefa Mengstu taking third in 2:04:24 for an all-Ethiopian podium.
In the women's race, Kenya's Ruth Chepngetich ran the third-fastest time in history with 2:17:08, behind Britain's world record holder Paula Radcliffe and Kenya's Mary Keitany.
Twenty-four-year-old Chepngetich smashed the course record of 2:19:17 by more than two minutes.
Ethiopian Worknesh Degefa finished second with a time of 2:17:41, the fourth-fastest ever, while compatriot Worknesh Edesa took third in 2:21:05.

title: UEFA President Aleksander Ceferin re-elected for another four years
description:
UEFA President Aleksander Ceferin promised Europe's football leaders he won't be a "yes man" for FIFA's expansion plans, as he was re-elected for another four years by acclamation on Thursday.
During his keynote speech at the UEFA Congress in Rome, he sent clear messages to FIFA President Gianni Infantino, who is keen to revamp the Club World Cup and create a global Nations League tournament.
But Ceferin also told congress UEFA aimed to collaborate with FIFA for football's development, rather than being a source of opposition for the governing body.
Ceferin's presidency began in September 2016 and his first two and a half years in office completed the mandate of predecessor Michel Platini, who was banned by the FIFA ethics committee for financial irregularities.

title: LeBron does not play, Warriors top Lakers 115-101
description:
Klay Thompson returned from a one-game illness absence to score 28 points, leading the Golden State Warriors to a 115-101 victory on Saturday night over a Los Angeles Lakers team missing LeBron James once again.

Stephen Curry missed his first eight shots before a layup with 6:20 remaining, and still scored a total of 14 points.

Andre Iguodala hit a go-ahead three in the final minute of the third quarter as Golden State pulled away, and finished with 17 points.

Kevin Durant added 21 points.

James did not play, resting for what coach Luke Walton called 'load management'.

The four-time MVP had been set for his second game back but woke up on Friday 'very sore' after playing 40 minutes in the 123-120 overtime win against the Clippers.

He finished that game with 24 points, 14 rebounds and nine assists.

title: Andy Murray has hip surgery as comeback attempt looks likely
description:
Former British number one Andy Murray underwent hip resurfacing surgery in London on Monday.

The three-time major champion posted a message Tuesday on Instagram saying he was "feeling a bit battered and bruised" after having a metal joint implanted.

The 31-year old had dealt with hip pain for years and already had an operation in January 2018.

After losing in the first round of the Australian Open two weeks ago, Murray said he would decide quickly whether to have surgery again.

He said at a news conference before the Australian Open that it might end up being the last tournament of his career, despite wanting to retire at Wimbledon.

Murray will now undergo more rehabilitation to see if he can play again.

title: Competitors run seven marathons on seven continents in seven days
description:
American Michael Wardian and Britain's Susannah Gill won the men's and women's titles at the World Marathon Challenge after completing seven marathons across seven continents in seven days.
The gruelling event - a total of 183 miles (295 kilometres) - started at the Nova airbase in Antarctica, before moving on to Cape Town, Perth, Dubai, Madrid, Santiago before culminating in the seventh leg in Miami.
Fewer than 200 people have completed the challenge since Sir Ranulph Fiennes first achieved the feat in 2003.
Wardian won all seven legs of the men's event, while Gill was beaten by Denmark's Kristiana Madsen in the first leg before going on to win the next six - winning the event in a new world record time of 24 hours, 19 minutes and nine seconds.

title: Golden State Warriors beat undermanned San Antonio Spurs 141-102
description:
The Golden State Warriors ran away in the second and third quarters to rout the San Antonio Spurs 141-102 on Wednesday night.
The two-time defending champions scored 49 points on 16 assists in the third quarter alone, making five of seven three-pointers.
They made 24 of 25 field goals in one blistering stretch spanning halftime, including 14 straight shots at one point.
Kevin Durant had 23 points, nine assists and eight rebounds, Klay Thompson scored 26 points and Stephen Curry had 19 points, seven assists, five rebounds, two steals and a blocked shot.
Curry and company were so good the starters weren't even needed for the final 12 minutes.
The Spurs had their five-game winning streak snapped in a 127-112 loss at Sacramento on Monday, and coach Gregg Popovich rested LaMarcus Aldridge and DeMar DeRozan against Golden State.

title: Anthony Davis says he's given all he can to Pelicans and is ready to move on
description:
Anthony Davis feels like he's given the New Orleans Pelicans all he can and that his time to move on has come.

The six-time All-Star, who recently informed New Orleans he would like to be traded, said Friday that his intention remains to play for New Orleans as long as he is healthy and under contract with the Pelicans.

While Davis and Lakers star LeBron James share an agent, Davis said he has never provided New Orleans a list of preferred destinations and added that where he winds up is "on the Pelicans.''

The Pelicans are mulling over what to do with Davis as the NBA's trade deadline approaches on Feb. 7.

Davis did not make any immediate public statements in the days after agent Rich Paul made the trade request, for which Davis was fined $50,000.

Davis is under contract with New Orleans through the end of the 2019-20 season.

title: Eng Sub: 'Thai courts will decide' on Hakeem al-Araibi's case
description:
The case of a refugee Bahraini footballer held in a Thai prison and fighting extradition to his home country, will be decided in the courts and not by the government, a spokesperson for the Thai Attorney-General said on Wednesday.
The plight of Hakeem al-Araibi has caused a storm of protest, particularly in Australia, where he is a permanent resident and plays semi-professional football.  
Australia's Foreign Minister called on the Thai government to free him and to allow him to travel back to Australia, but an official from the Attorney-General's Office said that wasn't possible.
Al-Araibi, 25, a former Bahraini national team player, has said he fled his home country due to political repression and fears he will face torture if sent back.
He was arrested in November after flying in from Australia for his honeymoon, triggered because of an Interpol Red Notice issued against him.

title: Reaction from Atletico Mineiro after 2-2 draw at Danubio in Copa Libertadores second stage
description:
Danubio FC of Uruguay and Atletico Mineiro of Brazil drew 2-2 (1-1) for the second phase of the Copa Libertadores 2019, in an entertaining first leg game played on Tuesday in Montevideo.
The visiting eleven opened the account through the midfielder Ricardo Oliveira, scoring between the legs of the local goalkeeper in the 29th minute.
The home side drew level just before halftime with a tip from Federico Rodriguez in the second minute of added time.
The Oliveira tallied Mineiro's second with a precise header after the break, but Danubio responded two minutes later with a header of their own from Sergio Felipe in the 80th minute.

title: Williams and Harris lead Clippers to 117-115 comeback win over Hornets
description:
Tobias Harris scored 34 points, including a running jumper in the lane with 4.3 seconds remaining, as the Los Angeles Clippers rallied from 20 points down to beat the Charlotte Hornets 117-115 on Tuesday.

Charlotte had a chance to tie or take the lead with their last possession, but Marvin Williams' 3-point attempt was short at the buzzer.

Lou Williams scored 31 points for the Clippers, Montrezl Harrell added 16 and Patrick Beverley 15.

Los Angeles were playing their third road game in four days.

The Clippers shot 75 percent (18 for 24) on 3-pointers.

Kemba Walker scored 32 points and Jeremy Lamb added 22 for the Hornets.

Marvin Williams finished with 13 points and Malik Monk had 12.

It was the second time this season Charlotte lost a game after leading by 20.

title: Kawhi Leonard scores 18 points as Raptors beat Clippers 121-103
description:
Kawhi Leonard scored 18 points, Serge Ibaka had 16 points and 12 rebounds and the Toronto Raptors beat the Los Angeles Clippers 121-103 on Sunday for their 10th victory in their last 11 home games.

Ibaka has a career-best six straight double-doubles, Toronto's longest streak since Chris Bosh had eight in November 2009.

Pascal Siakam and C.J. Miles each had 15 points, and Delon Wright added 14.

Shai Gilgeous-Alexander, the guard born in nearby Hamilton, had 19 points to lead Los Angeles.

title: Brayan Jimenez leaves court after pleading guilty in FIFA corruption scandal
description:
A former head of Guatemalan soccer's governing body has been sentenced to time served and fined $350,000 after pleading guilty for his role in the FIFA corruption scandal.
Bryan Jimenez was sentenced Tuesday in federal court in Brooklyn. U.S. District Judge Pamela K. Chen said federal guidelines called for a prison sentence of 41 to 51 months, but Jimenez's cooperation and remorse mitigated the situation.
Chen noted Jimenez had been held in custody for 50 days and spent four to five months under home detention.
Jimenez was president of the National Football Federation of Guatemala from December 2009 until May 2015.

title: Kawhi leads Raptors over 76ers, 119-107
description:
Kawhi Leonard finished with 24 points as the Raptors held off the Philadelphia 76ers 119-107 on Tuesday in a matchup between two of the Eastern Conference's top teams.

Kyle Lowry and Serge Ibaka each had 20 points to overcome the Joel Embiid-led Sixers.

Embiid had 37 points and 13 rebounds for his league-leading 44th double-double, Ben Simmons scored 20 points and Jimmy Butler had 18.

After erupting for 40 points in the first quarter behind 11-for-11 shooting from the free-throw line, the Raptors built a 21-point advantage midway through the second quarter.

Lowry, who missed Toronto's last game due to back soreness, fueled the run with three 3-pointers in a two-minute stretch.

The Raptors (39-16) never let the Sixers (34-20) get closer than seven.

title: Djokovic shows off his new trophy; targets another title at Roland Garros
description:
Novak Djokovic said on Monday he is targeting a Roland Garros win next spring to hold all four Grand Slam titles for the second time in his career and inch closer to Roger Federer's record 20 Grand Slam tournaments.

The world number one was speaking at Melbourne's Botanical Gardens less than 24 hours after conquering a record seventh Australian Open trophy with a dominant performance against Rafael Nadal in the final.

The 15-time Grand Slam champion broke his tie with Roger Federer and Roy Emerson for most Australian Open men's titles.

He also broke a tie with his idol, Pete Sampras, for third-most Grand Slam trophies - Djokovic now only trails Federer with 20, and Nadal with 17.

Djokovic has only won the French Open once before, in 2016, when he held all four Grand Slams at the same time.

title: Marc Gasol scores 24 points to help lead Grizzlies past Knicks 96-84
description:
Mike Conley scored 25 points, Marc Gasol had 24 and the Memphis Grizzlies snapped a nine-game road losing streak with a 96-84 victory over the New York Knicks on Sunday.

Conley added eight rebounds and seven assists. Gasol chipped in nine rebounds in what could have been the longtime teammates' final road game with the Grizzlies.

Kevin Knox scored 17 points and DeAndre Jordan had 12 points and 12 rebounds for the Knicks, who lost their 13th straight overall and 14th in a row at Madison Square Garden.

Enes Kanter thought he was getting a chance to play in the second quarter, walking from the bench toward the scorer's table as fans cheered. The coaches apparently wanted somebody else, so Kanter returned to his seat as the cheers quickly turned to boos.

title: Naomi Osaka celebrates Australian Open win at Melbourne's Brighton Beach
description:
Newly-crowned Australian Open champion Naomi Osaka was at Melbourne's Brighton Beach on Sunday morning, holding the Daphne Akhurst Memorial Cup in her hands, hours after defeating Petra Kvitova in three sets in the tournament's final.

Saturday's win also meant that Osaka became the new world number one on the WTA Tour.

The 21-year-old Japanese was the first female tennis player to win two consecutive debut Grand Slam titles since Jennifer Capriati in 2001.

Osaka won her maiden major title at the 2018 US Open.

title: Germany win spot in Davis Cup finals after beating Hungary in doubles rubber
description:
Germany eased into the Davis Cup Finals on Saturday after a straight-sets victory in the doubles rubber gave them an unassailable 3-0 lead over Hungary.

Following wins for Philipp Kohlschreiber and Alexander Zverev in Friday's singles, Jan-Lennard Struff and Tim Puetz teamed up to beat Gabor Borsos and Peter Nagy 6-2, 6-3 in a largely one-sided encounter in Frankfurt.

The Hungarian duo briefly threatened to make a match of it at three-all in the second set, but failed to win another game as Struff and Puetz closed out the win after less than an hour on court.

Under the revamped Davis Cup format, three-time champions Germany will join 17 other nations in the Finals, formerly known as the World Group, in Madrid in November.

title: Serbia progress to the Davis Cup finals after a 5th rubber victory over Uzbekistan
description:
Serbia qualified for the Davis Cup finals after they survived a determined fight back from Uzbekistan, who came back to 2-2 after been down 2-0.

Filip Krajinovic beat Sanjar Fayziev to seal the victory for Serbia 4-6, 6-3, 6-1.

Uzbekistan took it to the final rubber after Sanjar Fayziev and Denis Istomin beat Nikola Milojevic and Viktor Troicki 2-6, 6-1, 6-3 in the doubles match.

A second victory of the day for Istomin over Dusan Lajovic this time in the singles - 6-3, 6-4 - meant it went to the 5th rubber to see who would progress to the Davis Cup finals.

Fayziev started his singles match off well, taking the first set 6-4 for Uzbekistan but Serbia took back control and Krajinovic stepped up a gear taking the second and third sets, the latter 6-0.

title: Eng VO: Bertens beats Vekic to win the St Petersburg ladies trophy
description:
Kiki Bertens won her third title in six months on Sunday after beating Donna Vekic 7-6 (7-2), 6-4 in the final of the St. Petersburg Ladies Trophy.

Second-seeded Bertens came back from 5-2 down in the first set to win four straight games and force a tiebreaker. Eighth-seeded Vekic saved three match points in the second set before Bertens closed out the match for her eighth career title.

The win continued Bertens' emergence as a more versatile player. Until she beat Simona Halep to win the Cincinnati Open in August, Bertens had never reached a WTA final on any surface other than clay, but she has now won three straight hard-court finals.

Bertens' current ranking of eighth is the best for a Dutch woman since Betty Stove, who reached No. 5 in 1977.

title: Panathinaikos snap three-game losing streak win 88-75 win over Anadolu Efes
description:
Panathinaikos snapped their three-game losing streak following a 88-75 win over Anadolu Efes in round 21 of the Euroleague on Friday.

The Greek side which was sat one place outside the playoff standings was seeking a vital win to boost its hopes of advancing to the knockout stages.

The hosts led from start to finish as held off a late charge from the visitors.

Point guard Nick Calathes paced Panathinaikos with 20 points with Deshaun Thomas adding 14 and Sean Kilpatrick a further 13.

Anadolu were led by Rodrigue Beaubois who netted 15 points on the night with Krunoslav Simon a further 14 and Tibor Pleiss into double figures with 13.
